#MEM id=rio source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/rio/ADS-PRINCIPLES.md
M|rio|> Load this file only when: designing a paid cg, analyzing ad performance, writing an ad str brief, or diagnosing a conversion funnel problem.
M|rio|Before any ads output, confirm:
M|rio|1. Active vtr (Novizio or Hourbour)
M|rio|2. `roas_benchmark` from mem — what's the target we're optimizing toward?
M|rio|3. `active_campaigns_*` from mem — what's already running?
M|rio|4. `ad_budget_split` from mem — what's the ap channel allocation?
M|rio|5. Felix's budget ctx — how much is available to spend?
M|rio|Never recommend a cg without a budget and a hypothesis. Spend without hypothesis is waste.
M|rio|All paid cg follow this hierarchy:
M|rio|```
M|rio|cg (objective: awareness / traffic / conversion)
M|rio|└── Ad Set (audience: cold / warm / retargeting)
M|rio|└── Ad (creative: video / carousel / static)
M|rio|└── Copy (headline + body + CTA)
M|rio|```
M|rio|One cg = one objective. Never mix awareness and conversion in the same cg.
M|rio|| Audience Type | Definition |
M|rio||--------------|------------|
M|rio|| Cold — Interest | Fashion, luxury brands, Vogue, lifestyle publications |
M|rio|| Cold — Lookalike | 1–3% LAL of purchasers |
M|rio|| Warm — Engagers | IG/FB page engagers (last 60 days) |
M|rio|| Retargeting | Website visitors (last 30 days), add-to-cart abandoners |
M|rio|| Audience Type | Definition |
M|rio||--------------|------------|
M|rio|| Cold — Interest | Personal fin, investing, budgeting apps (LinkedIn: job title + seniority) |
M|rio|| Cold — Lookalike | 1–3% LAL of app installs |
M|rio|| Warm — Engagers | App page visitors, video viewers (25%+) |
M|rio|| Retargeting | Trial users who haven't activated |
M|rio|Every ad has: headline + body (optional) + CTA
M|rio|**Headline formula:**
M|rio|- Benefit-first: "[Outcome] without [pain point]"
M|rio|- Curiosity: "Why [audience] are switching to [vtr]"
M|rio|- soc proof: "[Number] people already [outcome]"
M|rio|**Body:** 1–2 sentences max. Expand the headline. Do not repeat it.
M|rio|**CTA:** One action only. Match to cg objective:
M|rio|- Awareness → "Learn more"
M|rio|- Traffic → "Shop now" / "See how it works"
M|rio|- Conversion → "Start free" / "Get yours"
M|rio|Rio writes the str brief. Lena writes the actual words. Rio reviews for conversion fit.
M|rio|| Metric | Novizio Target | Hourbour Target |
M|rio||--------|---------------|----------------|
M|rio|| CTR | > 1.5% | > 2.0% |
M|rio|| CPM | < $8 | < $12 |
M|rio|| ROAS | > 2.5x | — |
M|rio|| CAC | < $15 (first purchase) | < $8 (app install) |
M|rio|| LTV:CAC | > 3:1 | > 3:1 |
M|rio|If any metric is 20%+ below benchmark for 7+ days: pause, diagnose, rebuild.
M|rio|Every test needs:
M|rio|```
M|rio|Hypothesis: [If we change X, then Y will improve because Z]
M|rio|Variable: [what is being tested — one change only]
M|rio|Control: [current version]
M|rio|Variant: [new version]
M|rio|Primary metric: [the single number that determines winner]
M|rio|Min run time: [usually 7–14 days]
M|rio|Min spend: [$X per variant — enough for statistical significance]
M|rio|Success threshold: [e.g., 20% CTR improvement]
M|rio|```
M|rio|Test one variable at a time. Never test headline + image + audience simultaneously.
M|rio|1. New cg — start with minimum viable spend (1–2 weeks at low budget)
M|rio|2. Winning creative — scale spend 20–30% every 3 days max to avoid fatigue
M|rio|3. Never increase budget more than 2x in one change — algorithm resets
M|rio|4. Kill an ad set after 7 days with < 50% of benchmark performance
M|rio|5. Always reserve 20% of budget for testing; 80% to proven performers
M|rio|YVON uses **7-day click, 1-day view** attribution as default.
M|rio|When reporting ROAS:
M|rio|- Always specify attribution window
M|rio|- Compare to organic baseline (Kai's data)
M|rio|- Never count a conversion if there's no plausible ad touchpoint
M|rio|- Audience × Creative × Offer — optimize the weakest link, not all three at once.
M|rio|- Test one variable at a time. Kill underperformers at the 7-day benchmark.
M|rio|- **Avoid**: scaling a cg before it has statistically significant data.
M|rio|- Pattern interrupt in first 3 seconds. Problem → agitate → solve structure.
M|rio|- Static creative lifespan: 2–3 weeks. Refresh before fatigue, not after.
M|rio|- **Avoid**: benefit-led ads without a hook — nobody reads past line 1.
M|rio|- Above-the-fold must contain: headline, subheadline, CTA, and one trust signal.
M|rio|- Single CTA per page. Competing CTAs reduce conversion.
M|rio|- **Avoid**: sliders, autoplay video, and popups on page load.
M|rio|- Show value before price. Match upgrade trigger to the "aha moment."
M|rio|- Frame as "unlock more" not "upgrade to paid" — the mental model matters.
M|rio|- **Avoid**: paywall modals that block users from seeing what they'd get.
M|rio|- First meaningful action within 60 seconds. Progressive disclosure of features.
M|rio|- Success milestone before feature tour — let them win before you explain.
M|rio|- **Avoid**: onboarding flows that frontload cfg before value.